# RevealJS Presentation Style Guidelines

This rule ensures consistent styling and formatting across all slides in the RevealJS presentation.

## Structure Guidelines
- Follow the existing section/slide structure in [index.html](mdc:index.html)
- Maintain consistent heading levels (h1 for main titles, h2 for subtitles)
- Each main topic should have its own section with the `data-transition` attribute
- Use the `<!-- .element: class="fragment" -->` syntax for animated elements

## Styling Patterns
- Use `.bg-header` class for headers as shown in [custom/custom-styles.css](mdc:custom/custom-styles.css)
- Highlight important terms with `<span class="highlight">term</span>`
- For layouts, use the `.container` and `.col` classes
- Code snippets should use `<pre><code>` tags with appropriate language class
- Images should include `width` and `height` attributes

## Content Guidelines
- Keep bullet points concise and focused
- Use the SNU logo in the bottom-right corner for branding
- Reference [custom/custom-styles.css](mdc:custom/custom-styles.css) for consistent styling
- For interactive elements, utilize the functions in [custom/custom-scripts.js](mdc:custom/custom-scripts.js)

When adding new slides, maintain visual consistency with existing slides to create a cohesive presentation.
